饭

Character forms: 饭 U+996D , &#39277; CJK UNIFIED IDEOGRAPH-996D ← 饬 [U+996C] CJK Unified Ideographs 饮 → [U+996E]


Glyph origin:
Simplified from 飯 ( 食 → 饣 ).


Definitions:
For pronunciation and definitions of 饭 – see 飯 (“any cooked grain ; cooked rice ; etc.”). ( This character is the simplified form of 飯 ). Notes: Simplified Chinese is mainly used in Mainland China, Malaysia , and Singapore. Traditional Chinese is mainly used in Hong Kong, Macau , and Taiwan.
