Etymology:
Compare Proto-Mon-Khmer *puuŋ ( “ cooked rice ” ) , whence Mon ပုၚ် ( pɜŋ , “ cooked rice ” ) ( Ferlus, 1988 ).
Pronunciation 1 is the exopassive derivation of pronunciation 2, meaning "what is eaten" ( Schuessler, 2007 ).


